A phased migration approach reduces risk and ensures operational continuity.

Phase 1: Cloud Readiness Assessment
- Infrastructure review
- Workload dependency analysis
- Cloud suitability evaluation

Phase 2: Architecture and Design
- Target AWS service mapping
- Network and security baseline definition

Phase 3: Migration Execution
- Data migration preparation
- SAP workload deployment on AWS infrastructure

Phase 4: Validation and Testing
- Performance benchmarking
- Security and compliance validation

Phase 5: Post-Migration Optimization
- Cost monitoring and right-sizing
- CloudWatch-based operational monitoring
